Package com.geodesk.feature.filter

Class CrossesFilter

java.lang.Object
com.geodesk.feature.filter.CrossesFilter
All Implemented Interfaces:
Filter
public class CrossesFilter extends Object
A Filter that only accepts features whose geometry crosses the test geometry. Dimension of intersection must be less than maximum dimension of candidate and test - if test is polygonal, don't accept areas - if test is puntal, don't accept nodes This Filter does not accept generic GeometryCollections, neither as test nor as candidate (result is always `false`).

    • filterForTile

      public Filter filterForTile(int tile, Polygon tileGeometry)
      Description copied from interface: Filter
      Returns the Filter that should be used for the given tile. This allows a Filter to accept all features within a certain tile, reject a tile entirely, or substitute itself with a cheaper filter. This method will only be called if `strategy()` includes `FAST_TILE_FILTER`. Note that to signal that all features should be accepted, this method returns `null` (i.e. nothing is filtered out); to reject the tile entirely, it must return `FalseFilter.INSTANCE`. It can return `this` to indicate that no shortcut filter is available for the given tile.
      Specified by:
      filterForTile in interface Filter
      Parameters:
      tile - the tile number
      tileGeometry - the tile polygon (an axis-aligned square)
      Returns:
      the filter to use for this tile
